VIEW FILE CONTENT PAGE WISE : more FileName

SPLIT FILE INTO FILES BY N LINES IN EACH : split -l N FileName

SEARCH MULTIPLE MATCHING WORDS : egrep "Word_1|Word_2|Word_N" FileName

SHUFFLE FILE CONTENT : shuf FileName 

COUNT NUMBE ROF LINES IN FILE : wc -l FileName

COMPARE TWO FILES : cmp File_1 File_2

WHAT IS DIFFERENCE IN TWO FILES : diff File_1 File_2 

FIND A FILE IN LINUX : updatedb AND_THEN locate FileName

USE OF CALCULATOR : bc

DISPLAY CALENDER : cal

UPTIME AND USERS LOGGED IN : uptime

RECORD TERMINAL ACTIVITY : script AND_THEN ctrl d

COMPRESS FILE KEEPING ORIGINAL : gzip -k FileName

DECOMPRESS FILE : gunzip Filename.gz

COMPRESS FOLDER OR FIELS : tar -czf NewName.tar.gz File_1 Folder_N

DECOMPRESS TAR FILE : tar -xzf NewName.tar.gz 

ZIP MULTIPLE FILES : zip  File_1 File_N

LIST ALL SERVICES : systemctl list-units --type=service --all

PRINT ENVIRONMENT VARIABLES : printenv 

ADD NEW ENVIRONMENT VARIABLES : export VARIABLE_NAME=/Path/To/Value/

PRINT SPECIFIC Nth AND Mth COLUMN IN CSV FILE : awk -F , '{print $N, $M}' Filename

GET RANGE OF CHARACTORS OF EACH LINE IN FILE : cut -cM-N Filename

GET SPECIFC LINE FROM FILE : sed -n 'Np' Filename

REPLACE A SPECIFC WORD : sed 's/Old_word/New_word/g' Filename

CONVERT ALL LOWER TO UPPER CASE : tr [:lower:] [:upper:] < Filename

MAKE FILE OF DESIRED SIZE OF X MB : truncate -s XM Filename

PRINT VERTICALLY EACH LINE WIDTH N BITS : echo "Something" | fold -wN

CHANGE OWNER OF FILE : chown NewOwner FileName

CHANGE GROUP OF FILE : chgrp NewGroup Filename 

CHECK RAM INFO : free

CHECK CPU UTILIZATION : top

CHECK DISK UTILIZATION : du /Path/To/

CHECK FILE SYSTEM : df

CHECK HOSTNAME : hostname

CHECK CPU CORE THREAD INFO : lscpu

CHECK ARCHITECTURE : arch 

CHECK PARTITIONS AND DEVICES : lsblk

CHECK OS NAME : uname -a

CHECK IF PROCESS RUNNING : ps -ef | grep "Process Name"

GET PID OF PROCESS : pgrep ProcessName

STOP A PROCESS : sudo kill -9 PID

KILL A PROCESS : pkill ProcessName

LIST CURRENT JOBS : jobs

RESUME JOB IN BACKGROUND OR FOREGROUND : bg OR fg

RUN SCRIPT IN BACKGROUND : nohup /Path/ScriptName

CHECK IF PORT IP OPEN IN REMOTE SERVER : telnet IP PORT

CHECK ALL HUBS IN NETWORK PATH : traceroute Web_Link



